<H3> <TI>   Confirms Continued Supply of Defense Spares </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confirms Continued Supply of Defense Spares </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0706150294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0706150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia today expressed the hope that the forthcoming 
visit of the prime minister, Mr. Narasimha Rao, to Moscow will 
give a boost to economic and political relations between the two 
countries. 
  Addressing a press conference in New Delhi today, the deputy 
prime minister of Russia, Mr. Yuriy Yarov, said several 
agreements -- including investment guarantee pact and 
cooperation in science and technology -- will be signed during 
the visit. Responding to questions, he said Moscow gives 
priority to ensure uninterrupted supply of defense spares. On 
cryogenic engine technology, the Russian leader said experts 
from both the countries have reached an understanding for the 
supply of engines. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

