<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Chairs Cabinet Meeting on Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Chairs Cabinet Meeting on Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0706141894 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1325 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0706141894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 7 Jun (INA) -- President Saddam Husayn 
chaired a meeting of the Council of Ministers today. 
  During the meeting, his excellency stressed the need for the 
members of the Council of Ministers to directly follow up 
decisions and measures, to honor those who excel in applying 
them, to punish those who fail to apply them, and not to 
tolerate any poor performance or weakness in state-run 
institutions. 
  His excellency said: Ours is a state of the Ba'th Party and 
it should continue to enjoy the strength, enthusiasm, and vigor 
of youths. 
  His excellency also stressed the need to improve the 
standard 
of living of government employees, as well as the need to work 
out appropriate ways of transporting them to and from their 
departments and work sites and regulating office hours. 
  The Council also discussed a number of economic and 
organizational issues of interest to the citizens, and his 
excellency ordered that fruit and vegetable prices be watched 
carefully to guarantee balanced prices between producers and 
consumers. 
  His excellency called for developing and purifying seeds to 
plant them in a scientific way and to launch media campaigns to 
explain ways of preserving animal wealth. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

