<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Orders Increases in Sugar Beet Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Orders Increases in Sugar Beet Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0506141694 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0506141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God protect him, 
has ordered increases in the prices of sugar beets from 1,000 
dinars per tonne as follows, depending on the percentage of 
sugar available in the sugar beet: 
  Sugar beets that are 15 percent sugar shall be purchased for 
1,600 dinars per tonne. Sugar beets that are 14 percent sugar 
shall be purchased for 1,500 dinars per tonne. Sugar beets that 
are 13 percent sugar shall be purchased for 1,400 dinars per 
tonne. Sugar beets that are 12 percent sugar shall be purchased 
for 1,400 dinars per tonne. Sugar beets that 11 percent sugar 
shall be purchased for 1,100 dinars per tonne. Sugar beets that 
are 10 percent of sugar and below shall be purchased for 1,000 
dinars per tonne. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

