<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Orders Increase in Vegetable Oil Ration Quotas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Orders Increase in Vegetable Oil Ration Quotas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106114094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0106114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God watch over 
him, has ordered an increase in the ration quota of vegetable 
oil listed on the ration card, as well as the ration quota of 
vegetable oil supplied to the bearers of central market papers. 
  Trade Minister Dr. Muhammad Mahdi Salih told INA that leader 
President Saddam Husayn, may God protect him, has ordered the 
ration quota of vegetable oil listed on the ration card 
increased to 750 grams per month per person, instead of 625 
grams. The president also ordered an increase in the family 
quota listed in the central market papers to 2 kg of vegetable 
oil per month instead of 1.5 kg. The order of the leader 
president, may God watch over him, shall be implemented as of 
today, 1 June 1994. 

</TEXT>

