<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talabani Supports Barzani's Call for Disarmament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talabani Supports Barzani's Call for Disarmament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706172394 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0706172394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with KURDISTAN NWAY, which will be 
published tomorrow, Wednesday, brother Jalal Talabani, secretary 
general of the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan [PUK], said 
disarmament is essential. He added: We hope that Kurdistan 
will become a region where only the regular forces carry arms in 
defense of our borders. 
  Asked to comment on Kurdistan Democratic Party leader Mas'ud 
Barzani's proposal for the disarmament of Iraq's Kurdistan and 
its protection by the international community, brother Talabani 
said the PUK is ready to take the necessary steps to implement 
this sacred objective. He added: It is essential that we 
ourselves take this step under the supervision of the Kurdistan 
region government. We could form a committee made up of the 
interior minister, minister of the peshmerga affairs, and the 
director of the police corps to achieve this objective, he added. 
  Brother Talabani pointed out that expediting the 
normalization of the situation and ensuring the return of 
security and order to the sons of our people in Kurdistan would 
contribute to creating the atmosphere and necessary grounds for 
establishing the rule of law, democracy, and human rights. 

</TEXT>

