<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Vice Foreign Minister Makes Statement, Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Vice Foreign Minister Makes Statement, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606150294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PRC Vice Foreign Minister Tian Zengpei and his 
delegation left Damascus this morning at the end of a four-day 
visit to the Syrian Arab Republic. 
  He was seen off at Damascus International Airport by 
Assistant foreign minister Raslan 'Allush, a number of ranking 
Foreign Ministry officials, the Chinese ambassador in Damascus, 
and embassy staff. 
  Tian Zengpei made a statement to the correspondent of the 
Syrian Arab News Agency, SANA, in which he described his visit 
to Damascus as successful and one which contributed to 
bolstering bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation. 
  He said: During the visit, we had the honor to meet with 
President Hafiz al-Asad. We were also received by the foreign 
minister, and held a round of talks with the assistant to the 
foreign minister. 
  He added: We discussed several issues, bilateral relations, 
and international topics of mutual concern. The two countries' 
viewpoints on these issues were identical or close. 
  Tian Zengpei expressed satisfaction with the development of 
bilateral relations during the 40 years of diplomatic relations 
between the two countries and their efforts to further them. 
  The Chinese minister called for implementing UN resolutions 
on the Middle East crisis, especially Resolutions 242 and 338, 
realizing the legitimate rights of the Palestinian Arab people, 
and restoring all occupied Arab territories. He said: We 
appreciate Syria and its efforts to restore its occupied 
territories through peaceful means. We also greatly value the 
progress and achievements witnessed by Syria under the 
leadership of President Hafiz al-Asad, in the field of building 
the state, economic development, and boosting the people's 
standard of living. 
  He added: The international situation is witnessing a quick 
change, and Syria and China believe that there is a need for 
bilateral consultation. He also said: During my visit to 
Damascus, I conveyed a message, wishes, and greetings of 
President Jiang Zemin to President Hafiz al-Asad. I am also 
carrying a reply message from President al-Asad to President 
Jiang Zemin. 
  He said: In the message, the Chinese leadership expressed 
its readiness and desire to develop bilateral relations of 
friendship and cooperation. President al-Asad also expressed 
similar feelings and desire. 
  Concluding his statement, Tian Zengpei expressed thanks for 
the warm reception accorded to him, and wished Syria, under the 
leadership of President Hafiz al-Asad, more achievements, 
progress, and prosperity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

