<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Urges Yemenis To Respect Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Urges Yemenis To Respect Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0706191694 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0706191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Muhammad al-Amin Khalifah, the chairman of the 
Arab Parliamentary Union and the speaker of the Transitional 
National Assembly [TNA], has called on the brothers in Yemen to 
respect the cease-fire resolution to stop the bloodshed and to 
save the resources of the sons of Yemen. Mr. Khalifah expressed 
hope that the Yemenis will embark on an objective dialogue to 
arrive at a lasting solution to the crisis and an agreement 
acceptable to all the brothers in order to consolidate stability 
in their country and work toward reconstruction and development. 
  Khalifah pointed out that the Arab homeland, which has been 
observing the strife in Yemen, aspired to see the role of a 
strong and united Yemen in supporting the march of the Arab and 
Islamic nations, in light of the stability which would be 
achieved by its sons. 
  The chairman of the Arab Parliamentary Union called on the 
Arab parliamentarians to direct all their efforts towards 
containing the crisis, overcoming its negative effects, and 
supporting the peace and reconstruction efforts. He appealed to 
the brothers in Yemen on the need to heed the voice of reason 
and wisdom, for which they had been renowned, and to deny the 
opportunity to anyone intending to ambush the Arab and Islamic 
nation, endeavoring to squander its resources and destroy its 
unity. 

</TEXT>

