<F P=103> LD0706115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for our country's Foreign Ministry 
rejected the claim that Tehran supports one side of the conflict 
in Yemen and is dispatching military assistance to that country. 
He stated: From the start of the conflict the Islamic Republic 
of Iran clearly expressed its regret over the outbreak of the 
war and expressed its concern about the possible separation of 
the Muslim brothers in Yemen. He added: By adopting a neutral 
stance Iran has announced its readiness to mediate. 
