<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zahedan, Sistan-Baluchestan Prov., June 6, IRNA -- A 
relatively powerful sound bomb went off at the central market 
here at 19:55 hours local time (15:22 hours GMT) Monday. Eye 
witnesses said three people were injured and windows of the 
nearby building shattered as a result of the explosion. 
  Local officials are investigating the cause of the 
explosion. 

