<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, U.S. Ambassador Discuss Autonomy Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, U.S. Ambassador Discuss Autonomy Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    'Arafat Emphasizes Need for Funding </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706214294 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 7 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Yasir 'Arafat, president of the state of 
Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, this 
morning received Mr. John McCarthy the ambassador of the United 
States in Tunis. 
  During the meeting President 'Arafat received two important 
messages from the U.S. Administration pertaining to the current 
situation and the implementation of the Palestinian-Israel 
agreement and also the U.S. Administration's efforts with the 
donor states before the meeting scheduled for 9 June 1994. 
  The meeting was an opportunity to review the current 
developments of the take over of the Palestinian authorities in 
Gaza Sector and Jericho. 
  President 'Arafat had asked the donor states to speed the 
fulfillment of their pledges to enable the Palestinian National 
Authority to discharge their duties and implement their 
obligations in development and construction each of which is an 
urgent and fundamental necessity to strengthen the foundations 
of peace. 
  On his part, the U.S. ambassador expressed the interest of 
the U.S. Administration in the success of the peace process and 
in enabling the Palestinian authorities of discharging their 
duties successfully and as soon as possible. 
  The meeting was attended by Dr Sami Musallam, 
director-general of President Yasir 'Arafat's office. 

</TEXT>

