<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Yarov Meets With Rao, Signs Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Yarov Meets With Rao, Signs Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0806055294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0806055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia has reiterated its stand that the Kashmir 
issue should be settled between India and Pakistan bilaterally 
on the basis of the Simla Agreement and without any outside 
interference. The visiting deputy prime minister of Russia, Mr. 
Yuriy F. Yarov, said this during his talks with the prime 
minister, Mr. Narasimha Rao, in New Delhi yesterday. Mr. Rao 
appreciated Moscow's support to New Delhi on important political 
issues. He said he looks forward to his visit to Moscow and 
expressed the hope that a new chapter will be opened in 
India-Russian relations. 
  India and Russia have decided to set up five working groups 
to boost bilateral cooperation. The groups will be within the 
framework of India-Russian intergovernmental commission on 
trade, economic, scientific and technological cooperation. An 
agreement on this by the commerce minister, Mr. Pranab Mukherji, 
and the visiting Russian deputy prime minister, Mr. Yuriy F. 
Yarov, in New Delhi. The preliminary meeting of the commission 
will be held in Moscow in September this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

