  [Text] Paris -- U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
has said Syria seriously wants to push forward the peace talks. 
In an interview he gave in Paris to the U.S. CBS Network, 
Christopher noted that he will soon tour some Middle Eastern 
states, but he declined to set any date. 
  Yesterday, the U.S. State Department hinted that Christopher 
may tour some Middle Eastern states after attending a meeting of 
NATO foreign ministers in Istanbul next Thursday and Friday. 

