<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamic Jihad Leader Rejects Role in Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Jihad Leader Rejects Role in Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0706181594 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 7 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0706181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Muhammad Salamah] </F>
  [Text] Shaykh As'ad Bayyud al-Tamimi, leader of the Islamic 
Jihad Movement-Bayt al-Maqdis, has said that he has turned down 
an offer by President Yasir 'Arafat to accompany him to Jericho, 
viewing such a trip as accepting Israel's domination. 
  Asked by AKHIR KHABAR if he was offered a part in the 
Palestinian National Authority, Shaykh al-Tamimi said that 
President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] had contacted several 
Palestinian figures, including his son, Nadir al-Tamimi, 
offering them the portfolio of the Religious Affairs Ministry. 
Nadir, he said, is now in Tunis. 
  Shaykh al-Tamimi added: This is a personal contact rather 
than coordination between the Palestinian leadership and the 
Islamic Jihad Movement-Bayt al-Maqdis. 
  Asked whether Dr. Nadir has agreed to participate in the 
Palestinian Authority, Shaykh al-Tamimi said: Although this is 
a personal affair, I oppose it because such participation in 
principle means bargaining. Therefore, I urge Nadir to reject 
it. 
  He added: If the self-rule area is expanded to include the 
whole West Bank, I will agree to enter these territories to 
establish an Islamic opposition party, but not to participate in 
the Palestinian Authority. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

