<H3> <TI>   Arab Broadcasting Union Meeting Opens in Tunis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Broadcasting Union Meeting Opens in Tunis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706135294 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Under the patronage of President Zine El Abidine Ben 
Ali and at the invitation of the Tunisian radio and television 
company, the 17th session of the General Assembly of the Arab 
Broadcasting Union convened in Tunis today. The meeting was 
chaired by Foreign Minister Habib Ben Yahia who made a speech in 
which he conveyed to participants greetings from President Zine 
El Abidine Ben Ali and his good wishes for the success of the 
meeting. 
  He stressed that in the Tunisia of the new era, proceeding 
from awareness of the importance of joint inter-Arab action, we 
are seeking to host any inter-Arab activity, particularly those 
aimed at finding ways of fruitful cooperation and entrenching 
concord between the Arab states. 
  It should be underscored that at its morning meeting the 
General Assembly of the Arab Broadcasting Union elected 
Abdelhafidh El Hargem, director-general of the Tunisian radio 
and television company, as chairman of the Union and of its 
Executive Bureau. 

</TEXT>

