<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   ABU Session Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ABU Session Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906002294 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906002294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali received a 
cable from the participants in the 17th session of the Arab 
Broadcasting Union [ABU] general assembly held in Tunis on 7 and 
8 June 1994, in which they expressed their deepest gratitude for 
his agreeing that this session be held under his patronage and 
care. [passage omitted] 
  Participants have blessed the unanimous election of Tunisia 
for the chairmanship of the next session of the ABU and 
expressed confidence that the organization will secure more 
professional gains in response to the aspiration of Arab 
audiences. 
  The 17th session ended in Tunis last evening, which was held 
at the invitation of the Tunisian radio and TV enterprise. Held 
under the patronage of President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali, the 
session was attended by representatives of radio and TV 
broadcasting corporations from Jordan, the UAE [United Arab 
Emirates], Tunisia, Algeria, Saudi Arabia, Sudan, Syria, Iraq, 
Oman, Palestine, Qatar, Kuwait, Lebanon, the Libyan Jamahiriyah, 
Egypt, Morocco, Mauritania and Yemen. 
  At its opening session, the general assembly elected Mr. 
Abdelhafidh El Hargem, director general of the Tunisian radio 
and TV enterprise, as chairman of the assembly and of the 
executive bureau of the union. At the end of the session, Mr. 
Raouf El Basti from Tunisia was reelected director general of 
ABU for another four-year term. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

