<H3> <TI>   IDB Session Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDB Session Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806215594 Riyadh SPA in English 1930 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, June 8, SPA -- The council of executive 
directors of Islamic Development Bank (IDB) ended its 151st 
session here today under the chairmanship of Osama Faqih, the 
IDB president. 
  During its session, the council approved the bank's general 
budget, the independent annual budget for its programmes, the 
budget and plan for the Islamic research and training institute, 
an affiliate of the bank for 1415 ah [Arabic year from June 
1994-June 1995]. 
  The council approved a total financial lending of nearly 
83.5 
million U.S. dollars, which would benefit eight member states of 
the bank and three Islamic societies in non-member countries. 

</TEXT>

