<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Aide To Make First West Bank Visit Since '67 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Aide To Make First West Bank Visit Since '67 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0906090794 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 9 Jun 94 p 28 </F>
<F P=103> JN0906090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, AL-DUSTUR -- Nabil 'Amr, political adviser 
to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, will leave Amman today 
for the occupied Palestinian territories on his first visit 
since 1967. 
  'Amr said he will visit his relatives and hold contacts and 
consultations with Palestinian political forces and nationalist 
figures in the West Bank and Gaza Strip to pursue efforts made 
last year to set up a Palestinian democratic grouping. 
  'Amr said this grouping is a developed formula of the 
initiative proposed by 116 Palestinian personalities from inside 
and outside the territories in a memorandum that called for 
enhancing democracy in the Palestinian arena inside and outside 
the territories. 
  'Amr added that this initiative does not conflict with the 
fact that he is a member of Fatah or with his official duties in 
the PLO. 
  'Amr worked as director general of Palestinian radios for 10 
years, and then as a media adviser to the Palestinian president, 
and ambassador to the Soviet Union for five years. 

</TEXT>

