<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Pursues Hamas Squad Into Gaza Autonomy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0806150094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0806150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Eli Bohadana] </F>
  [Excerpt] A few hours ago, terrorists opened fire at the 
hothouses of Kfar Darom in the Gaza Strip, but nobody was hurt. 
An IDF [Israel Defense Forces] unit arrived on the scene and 
opened fire at the terrorists, who fled in two Peugeot 404's. 
  Last night, the IDF set out in hot pursuit of a Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] terrorist squad into the area of 
the autonomy. The three terrorists who opened fire at an IDF 
patrol fled in the direction of Rafah. Our forces did not 
sustain any casualties. During the pursuit, hundreds of local 
inhabitants gathered and threw stones at the soldiers in a bid 
to prevent them from catching the perpetrators. According to 
Palestinian sources, five local Palestinians were injured by IDF 
gunfire during this pursuit. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

