<F P=102>   EA0906102094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0906102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mr. Haydar Abu-Bakr al-Attas, the prime minister, 
had a meeting yesterday [7 June] evening with His Excellency 
Shaykh Zayid Bin Sultan Al Nuhayyan, the head of state of the 
United Arab Emirates [UAE]. During the meeting, the prime 
minsiter acquainted His Excellency Shaykh Sayid Bin Sultan on 
the latest developments of the situation in Yemen. He also 
explained to him the aims of his current tour of a number of 
Arab countries concerned with solving the Yemeni crisis. 
  During the meeting, His Excellency Shaykh Zayid Bin Sultan 
Al 
Nuhayyan expressed his sorrow for the continuation of the 
fighting and the danger of the escalation of the tragic 
situation in Yemen. He also expressed his hope that the Sanaa 
rulers will respond to the Security Council resolution which 
stipulates an immediate cease-fire and puts an end to the 
bloodshed in Yemen. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

