<F P=102>   EA0906101094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0906101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abd-al-Rahman 'Ali al-Jifri, deputy 
chairman of the Presidential Council, accompanied by brothers 
Sulayman Nasir Mas'ud, member of the Presidential Council, and 
'Abd-al-Qawi Muhammad Rashad, member of the Presidium of the 
National Assembly, this morning made an inspection tour of 
several residential quarters in Crater, al-Mansurah, Shaykh 
'Uthman, and Dar Sa'd in Aden Governorate. He also visited a 
number of police stations and acquainted himself with how daily 
life was proceeding and with the concerns and problems affecting 
the inhabitants as the result of their water supplies being cut. 
He also acquainted himself with the state of homes that had 
been damaged as the result of the random shelling by the [word 
indistinct] of the ruling military regime in Sanaa, to which a 
number of peaceful and innocent citizens had fallen victim. 
  The deputy chairman of the Presidential Council and those 
accompanying him also visited the Abyan front and met the 
commanders of the axis. They acquainted themselves with the 
progress of operations on the front, expressing the appreciation 
of the political leadership with the heroic steadfastness of 
those defending the territory of the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen and in defense of its brave people. 

</TEXT>

