  [Text] Our informed military sources in Sanaa inform that 
there is an obscure difference between the ranks of the 
commanders and officers in north Yemen on the issue of the 
failed war which was led by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih against the 
people in the Democratic Republic of Yemen. The information 
says that secret meetings were held during the last three days 
between the groups of the non-Sanhanian [not further identified] 
commanders, which made 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih issue orders to 
collect all the forces and means that remain with him and to 
raise his photographs [as heard] on them in 48 camps in an 
attempt to delude the others that he is still strong after it 
had become certain to him that his recent directives to enter 
Aden had failed. The sources confirmed that time for 'Ali Salih 
is no more gold [as heard] and he is now thinking of what will 
secure the establishment of the regime of the iron fist in Sanaa. 

