<H3> <TI>   Aden Reports Sanaa's `Intense' Contacts With Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports Sanaa's `Intense' Contacts With Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0806185694 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0806185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Informed diplomatic and political sources in Aden 
are certain that Iran's vigorous pursuit of the question of the 
islands and its threats against the United Arab Emirates [UAE] 
come within the framework of the total coordination, alliance, 
and solidarity between this state, known for its stern 
fundamentalist system, and the military ruling regime in Sanaa, 
which is backed by the tribal fundamentalist and extremist 
Reform Party. This party is known for its close links with the 
jihad movement and fundamentalist groups in the Arab states and 
elsewhere in the world. These sources express the view that 
constant and intense contacts are being maintained between the 
governments in Iran and Sanaa within a period of less than a 
week. 
  In this respect the two foreign ministers have met while 
officials in Sanaa, the last of whom was 'Abd-al-Wahhab 
al-Anisi, the secretary general of the Reform Party, have met 
the Iranian ambassador more than three times. The sources 
stress that the pressure brought to bear on the UAE is an 
attempt to shift it away from the clear stances it has adopted 
towards the destructive war launched by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
against the people in the south of Yemen. The sources are 
surprised by this alliance now formed between Iran and Sanaa, 
recalling that 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih stood strongly on the side 
of Iraq during its war with Iran and sent to Iraq over 10 
brigades to fight on Iraq's side against Iran. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

