<F P=102>   EA0906104094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0906104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Eyewitnesses have confirmed that the head of the 
ruling regime in Sanaa, 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, has personally 
executed a number of his military commanders and officers whom 
he had sent to the battlefronts, particularly those whose forces 
were routed under the blows of the forces of the young 
Democratic Republic of Yemen. The eyewitnesses, who arrived in 
Aden from Sanaa, said that the criminal, 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
had executed a number of commanders of the fronts in Kharaz, 
Karish, Tawr al-Bahah and Hadramawt. The eyewitnesses also 
confirmed that the fundamentalist, Colonel 'Ali Muhsin al-Ahmar, 
and the criminal Muhammad Abdallah Salih, 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih's 
brother, have executed many of the commanders and officers of 
the units providing supplies, provisions and communications 
after their failure to provide their units with the necessary 
supplies for the fighting, which was thought to last less than 
24 hours. 

</TEXT>

