<F P=104>  Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden -- AKHBAR AL-USBU' has learned that the 
security organs in the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] in Aden have 
arrested a number of Jordanians and prevented Jordanian families 
from leaving Aden for Jordan, under the pretext that Jordan is 
participating in the war at the side of President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih. It has also been learned that Jordan is holding 
intensive contacts through other parties to release the 
Jordanian nationals held as hostages. 
  Legal Jordanian sources said: What Aden has done is strange 
and a violation of international law. The sources added that the 
Jordanians are defenseless and have not participated in the war. 
Consequently, the sources said, the safety of the Jordanian 
nationals is the responsibility of the authorities in the south 
who should not restrict the movement of or arrest those 
Jordanians. 

