<H3> <TI>   Two Northern Aircraft Said Shot Down Over Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Northern Aircraft Said Shot Down Over Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906103894 Paris AFP in English 1016 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0906103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 9 (AFP) -- Two northern warplanes 
were shot down on Thursday [9 June] as they bombed Aden airport 
in south Yemen, witnesses said. 
  Four planes bombed the airport area, but one slammed into 
the 
sea and a second crashed into the city's residential Shaykh 
'Usman district after running into anti-aircraft fire, they said. 
  Northern warplanes launched a second raid half an hour 
later. 
  There were no immediate details of casualties. 
  Southern warplanes based at the airport have taken part in 
bombing runs to try to stop the northern advance on Aden which 
was declared the capital of an independent state last month. 

</TEXT>

