<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias Begins Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias Begins Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives on 2-Day Visit </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706160894 Tehran IRNA in English 1343 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 7, IRNA -- Greek Foreign Minister 
Karolos Papoulias heading a delegation arrived here Tuesday [7 
June] on a 2-day official visit and was greeted at Tehran 
Airport by his Iranian counterpart 'Ali Akbar Velayati. 
  Upon his arrival, Papoulias termed as "solid and strong" the 
relations between Tehran and Athens and called for their 
expansion. Papoulias said he as the foreign minister of Greece 
and head of European Unity's Council of Ministers, would hold 
talks with Iranian officials on expansion of bilateral relations 
and on various international issues. He expressed hope that the 
outcome of his talks in Iran would be "excellent". 
  The Greek foreign minister is carrying two messages from 
Greek President Konstandinos Karamanlis and Prime Minister 
Andreas Papandreou for Iranian authorities. 

</TEXT>

