<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Arrives in Rabat, Makes Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Arrives in Rabat, Makes Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806220894 Rabat RTM Television Network in Arabic 2030 GMT 
8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat RTM Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat arrived in 
our country this afternoon on a visit to Morocco. [passage 
omitted] 
  'Arafat is accompanied by a delegation made up essentially 
of 
Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, the culture minister, and Marwan Kanafani and 
Khalid Salam, advisers to the Palestinian president. 
  At the airport lounge 'Arafat made the following statement: 
  [Begin 'Arafat recording] First, you all know the 
deep-rooted, strong relationship which exists between us and his 
majesty the king, his rightly guided government, and his 
fraternal people. As is also known, we have for his majesty the 
king all the affection, all the fraternity, and all the strong 
brotherly feelings of which we are always proud. 
  We are about to leave for Palestine, God willing. We have to 
come and see the king in order to listen to his valuable advice 
and to his great wisdom which we, our people, and our nationals 
are in need of at this historic, critical, and important moment. 
God willing, we will pray together in the first of the two 
Qiblahs [Jerusalem], the third holy place, the place from where 
Prophet Muhammad, God's prayers and peace upon him, made his 
midnight journey to the seven heavens, and the birthplace of 
Jesus, God's peace be upon him. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

