<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat on Aid Message From Christopher </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat on Aid Message From Christopher </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906001694 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network Arabic 
2300 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906001694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network Arabic 
2300 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>




<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] As is well-known, Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat began a visit to Morocco today. 
  At the Rabat-Salle VIP lounge he made a statement in which 
he 
praised the stances of His Majesty King Hassan II toward the 
Palestinian issue, in particular, and Arab issues, in general. 
[passage omitted] 
  On the meeting of the countries offering aid to the 
self-rule 
areas that will begin in Paris tomorrow, the Palestinian 
president said: 
  [Begin 'Arafat recording] I received an important message 
yesterday from Mr. Warren Christopher on the occasion of the 
donor countries' conference, which--God willing--will begin its 
meetings in Paris tomorrow. This message demonstrates a 
clear-cut U.S. stance that is supportive of this process and the 
Palestinian authority. It urges all donor countries to follow 
the example of the U.S. Administration in offering urgent and 
immediate aid to the national authority to enable it to perform 
its duties, particularly because we need great potential in the 
first days to be able to carry this heavy burden. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

