<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German Parliamentary Delegation Arrives in Baghdad </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    German Deputy: Companies Ready To Resume Work </H4>

<F P=102> JN0806163294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1520 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0806163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 8 Jun (INA)--Dr. Ahmad Murtada, minister of 
transport and communications, today met with Dr. Erich Ridi 
[name as transliterated], member of the German Bundestag and the 
chairman of its Financial Committee. 
  During the meeting, Ridi expressed German companies' 
readiness to resume their activities in Iraq and to offer their 
expertise in all fields, especially in the fields of transport 
and communications. 
  He said that Iraq is a friend of Germany, and that it is 
very 
useful to deal with it. He commended the relations of 
friendship between the German and Iraqi peoples. 
  During the meeting, the two officials reviewed bilateral 
relations and ways of promoting them, especially in the fields 
of transport and communications. 

</TEXT>

