<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Continues in al-Sulaymaniyah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Continues in al-Sulaymaniyah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0906100194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0816 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0906100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Al-Sulaymaniyah, northern Iraq, 9 Jun (INA)--Pitched 
fighting has continued in various areas in the al-Sulaymaniyah 
Governorate between Jalal Talabani's troops on the one hand, and 
the forces of the so-called Islamic Movement and the gunmen of 
the Kurdistan Democratic Party allied with it on the other. 
  Today's edition of the newspaper AL-'IRAQ published here 
today quoted news reports originating in the al-Sulaymaniyah 
Governorate as saying that the most violent battles witnessed 
there were those waged in Qal'at Dizah, Banjwin, and Halabjah. 
The reports added that the gunmen of Mas'ud Barzani managed to 
kick Jalal Talabani's loyalists out of Qal'at Dizah and 
completely occupy the entire city after killing several of these 
loyalists. Jalal Talabani's loyalists fled the city, leaving 
behind them the bodies of their dead and wounded. Moreover, 
hundreds of citizens fled the city to neighboring villages and 
mountain caves, seeking shelter and safety. 
  The news reports also confirmed that battles continued in 
the 
areas surrounding the al-Sulaymaniyah Governorate. The elements 
of the so-called Islamic Movement, which supports Mas'ud's 
group, are attempting to control some areas inside the city of 
al-Sulaymaniyah, the reports added. Tension and fear spread to 
other areas and places in the Autonomous Region of Kurdistan 
because of the mistrust between the two groups of Mas'ud and 
Jalal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

