<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Allied Use of Arab Facilities Protested </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Allied Use of Arab Facilities Protested </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN Informed of Airspace `Breachings' </H4>

<F P=102> JN0406121894 Baghdad INA in English 0920 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0406121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, June 4 (INA)--Iraq has protested to the 
United Nations over continued breachings of its airspace by the 
American warplanes with purpose of provocation and surveillance 
and also dropping the flares. 
  In a letter to U.N. Secretary General, Dr. Butrus Ghali, 
Iraq's U.N. ambassador said that these warplanes had carried out 
a total of 681 sorties on May 20-31 over vast areas in the north 
and the south of the country and also violated the sound barrier 
and dropped flares that damaged the crops. 

</TEXT>

