<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brotherhood Members Said To Plan Regime's Overthrow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brotherhood Members Said To Plan Regime's Overthrow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906082294 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 1 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0906082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Najwa 'Abd-al-'Aziz] </F>
  [Text] Counselor 'Abd-al-Sami' Sharaf-al-Din, Public 
Attorney at the Higher State Security Prosecution Office, 
yesterday decided to remand in custody members of a Muslim 
Brotherhood organization for 15 days pending investigations. He 
ordered the items seized with the members to be sent for 
examination by forensic and laboratory experts. 
  Security men have arrested 11 members of the organization in 
several governorates. They include doctors, education experts, 
furniture dealers, students, and civil servants. Investigations 
conducted by District Attorney Sharif 'Abd-al-Nabi and Hisham 
Badawi with the organization members have uncovered secret cells 
formed by the organization in four governorates. According to 
the investigations, the new organization is an extension of the 
"Salsabil" organization uncovered a few years ago. The 
prosecutors charged members of the new organization with forming 
a consultative council, planning the overthrow of the regime, 
and preparing antiregime organizational documents and leaflets. 
The members used computers to keep information, and computer 
discs have been seized. The defendants informed officials on the 
remaining members of the organization in the other governorates. 
The prosecutors charged them with joining a secret organization 
that seeks to overthrow the regime. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

