<H3> <TI>   Cairo Police Sweep Nets `Fugitive Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Police Sweep Nets `Fugitive Terrorists' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0806135094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1310 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0806135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Jun (MENA)--A police sweep was carried out 
in southern Cairo's slum neighborhoods early this morning to 
apprehend fugitive terrorists, outlaws, and ordinary criminals. 
  Assistant Interior Minister Mansur 'Isawi said the sweep in 
which the various Interior Ministry departments took part 
resulted in the arrest of 12 men from the fundamentalist Islamic 
groups. He said that the sweep, which concentrated on the 'Arab 
Ghunaym area in Hulwan, also resulted in the arrest of 32 men 
from the Muslim Brotherhood and al-Salafiyun. Moreover, 20 
political suspects were arrested and referred to the State 
Intelligence Department. Some 16 ordinary criminals and outlaws 
were also arrested. Five pieces of various firearms were seized. 

</TEXT>

