<H3> <TI>   Syrian National Suspected of Infiltration Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian National Suspected of Infiltration Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0906103294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 9 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0906103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Muhammad Ibrahim, a 29-year-old Syrian citizen, was 
detained for 15 days on the orders of the 'Akko Magistrate's 
Court. The young man surrendered himself to Israel Defense 
Forces forces three days ago. 
  Our correspondent Yo'el Dar reports that the Syrian man is 
suspected of infiltrating Israel. He told the court that he 
fled Syria so as to receive medical treatment for scars left on 
his body by electric treatments he had been given by Syrian 
doctors. The judge ordered that the man be given a medical 
examination before a verdict is passed. 

