<H3> <TI>   Hashemi-Rafsanjani's Statement on Ron Arad Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hashemi-Rafsanjani's Statement on Ron Arad Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706183094 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The missing navigator Ron Arad has not been located 
in Iran. Iranian President 'Ali Hashemi-Rafsanjani said this in 
a news conference in Iran today. Rafsanjani emphasized that 
Iran has nothing to do with Ron Arad's fate. He also 
surprisingly declared Iran will not oppose the Middle East peace 
process in practice, despite its opposition in principle to any 
agreement with Israel. 
  A senior activist in the organization of Mustafa al-Dirani, 
who was abducted to Israel, said in Beirut today that Iran is 
actively aiding any organization hostile to Israel. 
  In reaction to Rafsanjani's comments, this evening, Israeli 
security sources said Israel continues to regard Iran and its 
satellites as responsible for Ron Arad's fate. 

</TEXT>

