<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chief of Staff on Peace, Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief of Staff on Peace, Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706190594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chief of Staff Ehud Baraq assesses that within one 
to one and a half years the political situation will clarify and 
we will know whether the region's leaders are ready to recognize 
Israel's security needs and reach normalization with it. If 
this does not happen, we will reach an impasse, according to the 
chief of staff. Lieutenant General Baraq also said that even if 
full peace and security arrangements are achieved, Israel will 
still need to preserve its military power and superiority for 
many years to come in the 21st century. He also said that 
terrorism will accompany us for a long time to come, and that we 
must also prepare to confront nonconventional dangers emanating 
from Iraq, Iran, and Libya. Our correspondent Haviva Roger 
reports that the chief of staff was addressing Haifa Technion 
graduates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

