<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aloni Warns of Labor Party Disintegration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aloni Warns of Labor Party Disintegration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706072194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706072194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister Shulamit Aloni has said that the Labor 
party is disintegrating and the functioning of all its bodies 
has been disrupted. Every wheeler-dealer wants to be a Knesset 
member and there is unbridled competition between hawks and 
doves, she said. Aloni cautioned that this disintegration might 
lead to the collapse of the peace process and to a war in which 
Egypt would also take part. According to her, Meretz must make 
the government's basic guidelines more pronounced and make sure 
that it abides by its commitments. 
  In response, Labor Secretary General Nisim Zvili told our 
party affairs correspondent Shmu'el Tal that Meretz's peace is 
not Labor's peace. He noted that Labor had been dealt a blow, 
but is currently recovering and not disintegrating. 

</TEXT>

