<H3> <TI>   Third Path Movement Warns of Possible `Revolt' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Third Path Movement Warns of Possible `Revolt' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706161994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The members of the Third Path have said they 
established their movement in defiance of the Labor Party and 
their own movement, the United Kibbutz Movement [UKM]. They 
wish to convey a warning that if Israel does not protect the 
Golan Heights, their movement will turn into an open revolt 
against Labor and the UKM, and they will consider establishing 
an independent party. 
  Our correspondent Shula Schmerling reports that the heads of 
the Third Path, who are members of the Golan kibbutzim, denied 
reports alleging they had received financial aid from other 
parties. According to them, all of their financial assets come 
from domestic sources, but refused to name them. 

</TEXT>

