<H3> <TI>   Ring Suspected of Selling Weapons to Fugitives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ring Suspected of Selling Weapons to Fugitives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706163594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, it was revealed that a network of 15 Jewish 
and Israeli Arab weapons dealers who sold weapons and ammunition 
to fugitives from the territories has been uncovered. Our 
correspondent Yafa Glick reports that the Tel Aviv Magistrate's 
Court today remanded two Netanya shooting gallery owners, Avi 
Hajaj and Shim'on Farhan, and one of the workers, Yosi 
Yankelevich. The three are suspected of having sold weapons and 
ammunition to six Israeli Arabs from al-Tira and Qalansuwa, who 
in turn sold the weapons to fugitives from Nabulus, Bayt Lahiyah 
in the Gaza Strip, and Tulkarm. 

</TEXT>

