<H3> <TI>   Minister Reaffirms Jordan's `Neutrality' on Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Reaffirms Jordan's `Neutrality' on Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0806132294 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 8 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM0806132294 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Jordanian Information Minister </F>
Stresses Amman's Neutrality in Yemeni Crisis"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Jordanian Information 
Minister Jawad al-'Anani has said that Jordan's neutral position 
on the Yemeni crisis has not changed since the crisis began, 
contrary to what some media services say. 
  In a statement to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT he added that "Jordan 
was 
aware early on of the dangers of an armed conflict in Yemen. It 
made great efforts with the two parties to the Yemeni crisis 
until we held a conference to sign the Pledge and Accord 
Document, which was tantamount to a defusing of the fighting and 
a step toward dialogue and a peaceful understanding. It was in 
response to a written request from President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih and his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid." 

</TEXT>

