<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Denies Making Statements on Syria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Denies Making Statements on Syria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0906063294 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1810 GMT 8 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0906063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asked by the Jordanian News Agency about statements 
attributed to him regarding the occupied Syrian Golan, published 
by the London-based newspaper AL-HAYAH yesterday, Prime Minister 
Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali has asserted that the statement 
attributed to him was untrue and distorted. 
  Dr. al-Majali added: We reject any attempts to distort our 
strategic relations with sisterly Syria. We deal with Syria 
with full confidence in the unity of both our objective and 
fate, and also out of the desire to reach a comprehensive peace 
that will safeguard the rights of all of us and secure the 
implementation of Security Council Resolutions 242 and 338, on 
which the peace process is based. 
  Dr. al-Majali said: We look forward to discussing all issues 
of mutual interest during the meetings of the Joint 
Jordanian-Syrian Higher Committee, which will be held in Amman 
at the beginning of next week in order to achieve the policies 
of the two leaders; namely, His Majesty King Husayn and his 
brother His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad, in a way that 
will achieve the utmost degree of cooperation and coordination 
between the two fraternal countries. 

</TEXT>

