<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kolesnikov, al-Shihabi Sign Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kolesnikov, al-Shihabi Sign Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0806182294 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 8 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0806182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sana' al-Imam from Damascus] </F>
  [Text] The Russian delegation led by Mikhail Petrovich 
Kolesnikov, the Russian Armed Forces chief of staff, left 
Damascus today. President Hafiz al-Asad received the delegation 
for two full hours. 
  The Russian Armed Forces chief of staff signed with his 
Syrian counterpart, Lieutenant General Hikmat al-Shihabi, 12 
documents related to cooperation in the technical military field. 
  Mikhail Kolesnikov, head of the Russian delegation, termed 
this as a new starting point in Russian-Syrian military 
cooperation. 
  These documents were signed against the background of the 
agreement on military cooperation in the technical field that 
was signed in April between Syrian Defense Minister Lieutenant 
General Mustafa Talas and Russian Deputy Premier Oleg Soskovets. 
This agreement has paved the way for the resumption of military 
cooperation between the two countries, especially since the USSR 
was the main exporter of arms to Syria before its collapse. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

