<H3> <TI>   Lithuanian Parliament Speaker Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lithuanian Parliament Speaker Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0806210394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 2015 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0806210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Ceslovas Jursenas, speaker of the Lithuanian 
parliament, and his delegation arrived in Damascus this evening 
on a four-day visit to Syria. 
  He was received at Damascus International Airport by 
'Abd-al- 
Qadir Qaddurah, speaker of the People's Assembly, and Shakir 
Is'ayyid, chairman of the Arab and Foreign Relations Committee 
in the Assembly. 
  Mr. Jursenas said upon arrival that he was glad to be 
visiting Syria. There have been no parliamentary relations 
between our two countries previously, he noted. During this 
visit, we want to get to know Syria first-hand and boost 
bilateral ties, particularly in parliamentary affairs, Mr. 
Jursenas told SANA. 
  This is the first time we have visited an Arab state since 
our independence. Our nation, he added, welcomes contacts and 
relations with Syria in particular and the Arab states in 
general. He emphasized that his country is particularly 
interested in the Middle East and the ongoing peace talks. 
Lithuania, he stated, supports the return of the occupied 
territory to its rightful owners. 
  The Lithuanian parliament speaker concluded his statement by 
saluting Syria and its people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

