  [Text] Jordanian Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali 
has denied the statements attributed to him regarding the 
occupied Syrian Golan, published by the London-based newspaper 
AL-HAYAH yesterday [as heard], saying that these statements were 
untrue and distorted. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency yesterday, Dr. 
al-Majali added: Jordan rejects any attempts to confuse its 
strategic relations with sisterly Syria. Jordan regards Syria 
with absolute faith in common objectives and destiny to reach a 
just and comprehensive peace that will safeguard the rights of 
all of us, and ensure the implementation of UN Security Council 
Resolutions 242 and 338, on which the peace process is based. 

