<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Orders Closure of PLO Offices in Tunisia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Orders Closure of PLO Offices in Tunisia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906213994 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As the Palestinian issue develops, and in 
preparation for the move to the self-rule area in Jericho, 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat ordered the closure of the 
PLO Central Committee's offices in Tunisia next week. 
  The source who announced the news said orders have been 
issued to more than 600 Palestinian administrative and security 
officials at the beginning of sthe week, pointing out that 
President 'Arafat will temporarily keep his offices and place of 
residence in the Tunisian capital. 
  The transfer process will not include the PLO Political 
Department, which is being kept in Tunisia to coordinate between 
the Palestinian national authority and the international 
community and to look after the affairs of the Palestinians 
living abroad. 
  The source neither specified the time of the move nor the 
number of officials who will accompany President 'Arafat to 
Jericho. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

