<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat May Visit Jericho at End of June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat May Visit Jericho at End of June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906180994 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 9 
Jul 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brother Faysal al-Husayni, member of the 
Palestinian National Authority, yesterday said that the 
Palestinian leader, President Yasir 'Arafat, could arrive in 
Jericho at the end of this month. Al-Husayni added that 
'Arafat's arrival depends on the results of today's meeting 
between Palestinian officials and officials representing donor 
countries in Paris. 
  The donor countries have pledged over $2 billion to the 
Palestinian self-ruled areas over a period of five years, but so 
far only $5 million have come from the United States. The 
latter had promised to give $500 million. 
  In a statement to the press, al-Husayni said that he could 
not give a precise date for 'Arafat's arrival in Jericho, but 
added: I hope that this will be in the second half of this month. 
  In reply to a question on whether the timing of 'Arafat's 
arrival is linked to the conference of donor countries in Paris, 
al-Husayni said: There is a link of this kind. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

