<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Husayni Reacts to Rabin Remarks on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Husayni Reacts to Rabin Remarks on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0906151394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1005 GMT 9 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0906151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister said this morning that Faysal 
al-Husayni would have to move to Jericho if he planned to run 
autonomy affairs. Surprisingly enough, Faysal al-Husayni did 
not reject the suggestion. Here is what he told Qol Yisra'el's 
English department correspondent Dick Winter: 
  [Begin recording] [Al-Husayni] I do not know if it was 
meant as a threat. In any event, if Mr. Rabin means that I 
should leave my home here and move to Jericho, I do not think it 
is a statement [preceding word in English] he should have made. 
  [Winter] What about your office? 
  [Al-Husayni] If he was referring to the offices, I have an 
office right here, where I conduct activities that are part of 
the peace process [preceding two words in English]. I will 
pursue that part which is not related only to the interim 
agreement. If, however, he was referring to activities 
pertaining to the Palestinian rule, then we can discuss the 
matter and see how to proceed. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

