<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jericho Mayor Resigns; Rumors of Arrest Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jericho Mayor Resigns; Rumors of Arrest Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1006102094 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 10 Jun 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> JN1006102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Muhammad 'Amirah in Jericho] </F>
  [Text] Jericho Mayor Jamil Sabri Khalaf has tendered his 
resignation to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat without 
stating the reasons. Although President 'Arafat rejected the 
resignation and asked Khalaf to remain in his post until general 
elections are held next month, Khalaf has decided to stay at 
home. 
  Lieutenant Colonel Munthir Irshayd, the Palestinian 
Administration official in Jericho, who was appointed to this 
position by 'Arafat after the implementation of the first phase 
of self-rule, has denied Israeli media reports about the arrest 
of the mayor. 
  In an exclusive statement to AL-DUSTUR, Irshayd said such 
Israeli rumors are part of Israel's psychological warfare and 
that the man (Khalaf) chose to stay at home without any coercion 
or pressure. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

