<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Says No Meeting Held With Husayn `This Week' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Says No Meeting Held With Husayn `This Week' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1006054994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 10 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1006054994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Rumors spread through 
Jerusalem last night that Prime Minister Rabin had recently met 
with Jordan's King Husayn. This followed a report broadcast on 
Israel's second television channel that the two leaders last 
week held talks in Washington. When later asked by reporters if 
a meeting with King Husayn took place, Rabin responded: I did 
not meet him this week. Sources close to the prime minister 
refused to deny or confirm the report. The Prime Minister's 
Office would not comment on the matter. Sources in Washington 
said Rabin had not been in the United States since last March. 
  Meanwhile, the office of Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres has 
denied claims that he met King Husayn earlier this month in 
Europe. Knesset Member Ra'anan Kohen raised the question two 
days ago in the Knesset. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

