<H3> <TI>   European Union To Release Loan Installment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    European Union To Release Loan Installment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906200194 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the satisfaction recorded by the European 
troika, the European Union is to order the release of a $150 
million loan to Algeria. The amount is the final installment of 
an overall loan of $400 million granted to Algeria in 1991. 
Algeria and four other countries will also benefit from loans 
from the Islamic Development Bank [IDB]. The IDB is to grant 
Algeria a $6.5 million loan to be spent on papier mache exports. 

</TEXT>

