<H3> <TI>   Zeroual Message Marks Zeralda Summit Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zeroual Message Marks Zeralda Summit Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906190694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Liamine Zeroual, head of state and current president 
of the Arab Maghreb Union, emphasized his determination to build 
a harmonious and prosperous Arab Maghreb in accordance with the 
aspirations of the peoples of the region. 
  In a message he addressed today on the occasion of the sixth 
anniversary of the Zeralda summit, Zeroual said that in the 
world of today, which is characterized by fast transformations 
and in which the weight of political and economic groupings is 
increasing, the Arab Maghreb should face the challenge 
represented by its union in order to occupy its rightful place 
in the new order of international relations. 

</TEXT>

