<H3> <TI>   Musa Message to Christopher on Bosnia Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Message to Christopher on Bosnia Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906123094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1145 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0906123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 9 Jun (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
urged U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher to support the 
nonaligned foreign ministers's call for convening an 
international conference on Bosnia to be sponsored by the United 
Nations. 
  This came in a message from 'Amr Musa to Christopher on this 
resolution. 
  Musa clarified that the objectives of this conference are to 
immediately apply the cease-fire and to put an end to all 
military activities under the supervision of the peace-keeping 
forces. In addition, the other objectives are to turn 
Bosnia-Herzegovina into a safe-haven and guarantee that the 
regional borders and sovereignty are not harmed. 
  MENA has learned that Musa sent a similar message to French 
Foreign Minister Alain Juppe and Douglas Hurd, British secretary 
of state for foreign and commonwealth affairs, about the 
extensive efforts Egyptian diplomacy is exerting to support the 
Bosnian cause. 

</TEXT>

