<H3> <TI>   U.S. Told To `Stop Interfering' in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Told To `Stop Interfering' in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906210194 Tripoli Libyan Television Network in Arabic 
1930 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0906210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Libyan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The United States has voiced great concern over the 
fighting in Yemen. A statement issued yesterday by the U.S. 
State Department speaks of mounting concern over the grave 
consequences of continued fighting in that country. The State 
Department's statement indicates that the United States is 
trying to involve itself in the situation in Yemen and dictate 
certain policies on that country. Instead of getting alarmed 
over Yemen, the United States would do well to stop interfering 
in its affairs and hatching plots against its unity. 

</TEXT>

