<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Delegation Visits for Economic Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Delegation Visits for Economic Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0906161994 Tel Aviv DAVAR in Hebrew 9 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> TA0906161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv DAVAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Moti Bassok] </F>
  [Text] An Israeli delegation headed by 'Oded 'Eran, 
Foreign Ministry deputy director general, is currently in 
Morocco discussing ways to improve economic relations between 
the two countries. 
  Jerusalem believes that despite the fact that King Hassan is 
still hesitant to establish diplomatic relations with Israel, in 
his meeting with Foreign Minister Peres last week he agreed to 
take energetic steps to improve economic relations between the 
two countries. 
  The Foreign Ministry delegation left for Morocco to prepare 
for Israel's participation in the talks of the working group on 
Middle East economic development in the framework of the 
bilateral talks. The deliberations of this committee will open 
in the Moroccan capital of Rabat next Thursday and will last 
three days. This will be the fifth round of talks for this 
committee, and it will be attended by 30 delegations, 14 of 
which will come from Arab countries. 
  The talks will mainly focus on the development of regional 
transportation in the Middle East, and cooperation between the 
countries on issues of tourism and agriculture. An effort will 
be made for the first time to informally discuss the 
institutionalization of cooperation. 
  The Israeli delegation will be headed by Prof. Ya'aqov 
Frenkel, Bank of Israel governor, and Uri Savir, Foreign 
Ministry deputy director general. It will also include 
representatives of the IDF [Israel Defense Forces], the Foreign 
and Finance Ministries, and the Bank of Israel. The delegation 
will also be accompanied by a group of Israeli reporters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

