<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Cooperation With Iran in Judicial Field </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Cooperation With Iran in Judicial Field </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0906210294 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1600 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0906210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 8 June (SUNA) -- Al-Sayyid Jalal Ali 
Lutfi, the chief justice, and those accompanying his excellency, 
returned to the country yesterday after visiting the Islamic 
Republic of Iran, where he held discussions with senior Iranian 
officials on joint cooperation in different judicial fields. 
  'Abd-al-Rahman Sharafi, a member from the delegation, told 
SUNA that the visit achieved its goal. He said that the chief 
justices of the two countries signed a memorandum of 
understanding on cooperation and coordination in the judiciary 
field and in international and regional forums, in addition to 
agreeing on other bilateral relations. He said that the Iranian 
Republic will provide the Sudanese judiciary with modern 
equipment and sufficient reference materials on Islamic 
jurisprudence. He added that an agreement was concluded on 
exchanging scholarships and training courses, in addition to 
(?providing) the Sudanese judiciary with [word indistinct] 
agricultural equipment and medicine necessary for the 
judiciary's service projects. 

</TEXT>

