  [Text] Honored listeners, an official spokesman at the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY] Defense Ministry has issued 
the following statement to the YEMENI NEWS AGENCY, Aden: At a 
time when the sons of our Yemeni people, brothers, and friends 
were looking forward to the declaration of the cease-fire, with 
effect from 1800 this evening, 9 June, in implementation of UN 
security resolution No. 924, and in response to the sincere 
efforts of Mr. al-Akhdar al-Ibrahimi, the UN secretary general's 
envoy to Yemen, our forces deployed on the Abyan and Lahij axes 
were subjected to a comprehensive surprise attack and 
concentrated artillery barrage, which was launched by the forces 
of the ruling military regime in Sanaa. This attack is still in 
progress. The Armed Forces of the DRY, which are absolutely and 
totally observing the cease-fire resolution in effect from 1800 
this evening, so as to prevent the shedding of Yemeni blood in 
respect and appreciation for the good and sincere efforts of the 
UN envoy, affirm to the masses of our people in the DRY their 
complete ability to repel the cowardly aggressors, and to force 
them into respecting the international authority and its 
resolutions. The Defense Ministry wishes at the same time to 
praise the good efforts resulting from the high degree of 
responsibility on the part of the UN envoy, and to appeal to the 
UN Security Council to take stern measures against this raging 
aggressor, who not only sheds the blood of our Yemeni people, 
but defies the will of the whole international community. 

</TEXT>

