<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, Yemen, June 10 (AFP) -- Northern heavy 
artillery gunners shelled the southern stronghold of Aden on 
Friday, a day after the collapse of the latest ceasefire in 
Yemen's civil war. 
  Shells crashed into the Khormaksar district, near the 
airport 
used by southern warplanes, an AFP correspondent said. 
Ambulances rushed to the scene, but there was no immediate 
casualty toll available. 
  The bombardment cut off electricity supplies to several 
districts of the capital of the south's breakaway state. 
[passage omitted] 

