<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Committees To Begin Assessing Damage, Extending Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Committees To Begin Assessing Damage, Extending Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0906165394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0906165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting was held at the Ministry of Planning and 
Development today with a number of the ambassadors to our 
country from fraternal and friendly states, as well as officials 
from certain international organizations. 
  Mutahhar 'Abdallah al-Sa'idi, deputy minister of planning 
and 
development, spoke at the meeting about the emergency needs 
faced by the country in the fields of health, water, sewage, 
electricity, and education that have resulted from the military 
operations carried out by the secessionist clique in the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] leadership. He said many of these 
facilities were damaged during these military operations. 
  He also spoke about the pressing need to extend urgent aid, 
food and shelters to the citizens who were harmed during that 
period. 
  'Awni al-'Ani, representative of the UN program in Sanaa, 
spoke during the meeting. He stressed the urgent need for this 
aid, hoping that these states will cooperate, either directly, 
or within the framework of the United Nations, to extend the 
necessary aid. He noted that committees to assess damages will 
begin their work as soon as possible to determine the actual 
needs. 
  The under secretary of the Public Health Ministry attended 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

