<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden's al-'Attas Says Arab States Aiding North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden's al-'Attas Says Arab States Aiding North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1006100694 Al-Dammam AL-YAWM in Arabic 8 Jun 94 p 25 </F>
<F P=103> JN1006100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Al-Dammam AL-YAWM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Engineer Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, "prime minister </F>
and finance minister in southern Yemen" by correspondents Falih 
al-Saghir and Sa'ud al-Rayyis; place and date not given] 
  [Excerpts] [AL-YAWM] How do you explain the Arab evasion 
concerning the recognition of the Democratic Republic of Yemen 
[DRY]? 
  [Al-'Attas] This is due to the ambiguities of the current 
situation. But now that the issue has been discussed by the UN 
Security Council, I believe the time is very appropriate for 
Arab and friendly countries to explicitly specify their stand in 
order to avert further destruction of our people, which the 
northern leadership carries out. [passage omitted] 
  [AL-YAWM] Do you believe recognition of the DRY will 
increase 
the chances of halting the war? 
  [Al-'Attas] Recognition will keep Sanaa from continuing what 
it insists on carrying out. 
  [AL-YAWM] What is the actual number of dead and homeless? 
  [Al-'Attas] There are no accurate figures about how many 
have been killed. But we estimate the number of dead at 60,000 
and those made homeless at hundreds of thousands. 
  [AL-YAWM] What do you have to say to Sanaa's statement that 
the southern forces were the ones to hit the Aden refinery? 
  [Al-'Attas] Two northern Air Force squadrons, each 
comprising 
four planes, raided the refinery. These are lies. It is very 
shameful for them to resort to such lies. [passage omitted] 
  [AL-YAWM] What about the shortage of medical and food 
supplies? Is there any assistance in this respect? 
  [Al-'Attas] The war in Yemen has resulted in an acute 
shortage of medical and food supplies. We do not have the 
medical supplies needed to treat those wounded in the war that 
was ignited by the Sanaa leadership against our people in the 
south. 
  There is also a shortage of food supplies as a result of the 
war that obstructs their shipment to southern Yemen. We appeal 
to our Arab brothers and our friends to send us medical supplies 
and food. 
  [AL-YAWM] Will you ask Sanaa for war reparations? 
  [Al-'Attas] Certainly. Although the war has harmed all the 
Yemeni people, the Sanaa leadership launched it. [passage 
omitted] 
  [AL-YAWM] Are there foreign elements other than the Iraqis 
within the northern forces? 
  [Al-'Attas] Yes, there are Sudanese elements, beside the 
Iraqis. Iraq assists the northern forces. Jordan also provides 
spare parts for aircraft and other equipment. We have 
information that they received new aircraft and spare parts for 
the Phantoms they have from Jordan. They also received other 
forms of technical assistance and pilots. We know the pilots 
that carry out the raids are not Yemenis but are Iraqis and from 
other nationalities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-36586 </DOCNO>
