<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Official Source' Welcomes U.S., Arab Stands on Sanaa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Official Source' Welcomes U.S., Arab Stands on Sanaa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0906120094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0906120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source in the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen [DRY] welcomed the American stand concerning the necessity 
of Sanaa's obligations to the UN Security Council's resolution 
on cease-fire and not to impose unity by force. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni news agency, Aden, the source 
also praised the communique of the Arab Gulf countries, members 
of the Cooperation Council, and the communique of the ARE [Arab 
Republic of Egypt] expressing thanks to the fraternals in the 
Gulf and Egypt for their positive stand which shows eagerness 
about Yemen's land and people. 
  The source added: We announce our thanks to the Arab 
community and the world community, which rejected the law of 
force, destruction and bloodshed, and we would like to confirm 
our obligation to the Security Council Resolution No. 924 and 
that Sanaa is trying to deceive the world just as it did in the 
night of the blessed 'Id al-Adha when it announced a cease-fire 
and gave its orders to its forces to resume fighting. 
  The source said: We are picking up signals of orders by the 
head of the Sanaa regime to these forces in the fighting fronts 
to regather and mobilize themselves in an offensive position on 
our country. And, as for us, we will commit ourselves to the 
resolution of the world community and we will not do any 
military action except in defense against the awaited attack. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

