<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden `Minister' Praises Kuwaiti Coverage of War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden `Minister' Praises Kuwaiti Coverage of War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0906202094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0906202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun, the minister of oil 
and minerals and military commander of the interior axis, 
praised the state of Kuwait's principled stand. He praised 
Kuwait's press for its covering of the events. Mr. Bin-Husaynun 
said in a contact with the AL-QABAS newspaper, published today, 
that the northern forces had attacked yesterday morning the 
southern forces at al-'Akbar/Askar axis, and that after violent 
fighting several northern tanks were destroyed and 11 soldiers 
were taken prisoner. Bin- Husaynun said that the battle on this 
axis had begun on 2 June, when the Maghawir forces tried to 
infiltrate into Khash'in al-Ayn, and were repelled by our forces 
after fierce fighting. Our Armed Forces destroyed a tank 
squadron and took 15 soldiers prisoner. The enemy ran away, 
leaving back a number of artillery, and killed and injured 
soldiers. Last Tuesday [7 June] the northern forces launched an 
attack, despite the cease-fire declaration. The enemy suffered 
the destruction of seven tanks, and the death of soldiers and 
imprisoning of others, and the shooting down of a MiG-21 
warplane. 

</TEXT>

