<F P=100> Western Sahara </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voter Identification for Referendum Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Voter Identification for Referendum Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906030894 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906030894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The United Nations has announced the postponement of 
the voter identification operation with regard to the 
self-determination referendum in Western Sahara. Our 
correspondent has more details: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Voter identification for those 
who are to take part in the self-determination referendum in 
Western Sahara, which was supposed to begin today in Laayoune, 
has been postponed until next week for logistical reasons. The 
United Nations announced the news from Rabat today, confirming 
that the transportation of Moroccan and Saharan notables to 
registration locations raised some technical problems. 
  According to a UN-Moroccan joint statement signed at the end 
of May in Rabat by the Moroccan interior minister and Erik 
Jenssen, acting special envoy of the UN secretary general, all 
Saharans concerned with the referendum had been informed that 
voter identification would begin today in Laayoune. 

</TEXT>

