<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Reduces Curfew Hours </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Reduces Curfew Hours </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0906180694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0906180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In view of the prevalence of security and stability 
throughout the governorates of the republic, and in light of the 
brother citizens' great and positive cooperation with the curfew 
instructions, the Ministry of Interior announces to all brother 
citizens throughout the governorates of the republic that it has 
been decided to reduce the curfew hours. As of today, Thursday, 
curfew hours will be from 2200-0500. Thus, all businesses and 
activities in all cities can proceed in accordance with this new 
schedule, which must be complied with. 
  The ministry wishes to explain that any party, institution, 
or individual whose jobs necessitate moving from one place to 
another during the curfew hours must obtain a special license 
from the Ministry of Interior. Motorists should always carry 
with them the documents that prove their ownership of the 
vehicles that they drive. 
  The ministry takes this opportunity to express thanks and 
appreciation to all citizens for cooperating with the security 
agencies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

