<F P=103> EA1206151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lieutenant General 'Umar Hasan Ahmad al-Bashir, 
the president of the Republic and commander in chief of the 
people's Armed Forces, attended the big popular rally organized 
by the citizens yesterday evening in front of general 
headquarters to mark the recapture of the town of Kajo Kaji. 
  The rally was addressed by Major Gen. Zuhayr Muhammad Salih, 
the first vice president of the Republic, who declared that the 
rebels still had the opportunity to enter into negotiations for 
the sake of construction and reconstruction. His excellency 
announced that peace was prevailing countrywide and that 
enormous numbers of rebels were surrendering to the Armed Forces 
at the headquarters of state governments. He said the time had 
now come to get caravans of support moving to realize and 
restore stability following the defeat of the rebellion. He 
added that the mobilization of the ultimate force currently 
being equipped would move in order to bring about construction 
and reconstruction. [passage omitted] 

